    "body": "Update, from the spec:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/phase0/beacon-chain.md#genesis\r\n\r\n```\r\ngenesis_time=eth1_timestamp - eth1_timestamp % MIN_GENESIS_DELAY + 2 * MIN_GENESIS_DELAY,\r\n```\r\n\r\n1587755000 - mod(1587755000; 3600) + 2 * 3600 = 1587762000\r\n\r\nWhich is 9:00:00 pm UTC if `eth1_timestamp` is equal or greater than `MIN_GENENIS_TIME` but @nisdas just explained me that `eth1_timestamp` can also be lower than that which might be the case here because I did the deposits significantly before `MIN_GENENIS_TIME`.\r\n\r\nForwarding that question to the Lighthouse team. @paulhauner Does your client do any checks to enforce `eth1_timestamp` to be greater than `MIN_GENENIS_TIME`? Or do you have any idea why Lighthouse computes a different genesis time than Prysm?",
