    "body": "This is the block: https://goerli.etherscan.io/block/2581357\r\n\r\nTimestamp is `1587752706` (6:25:06 pm UTC | Friday, April 24, 2020)\r\n\r\n```\r\n1587752706 - mod(1587752706;3600) + 2 * 3600\r\n= 1587758400\r\n```\r\n\r\nGenesis time is `1587758400` (8:00:00 pm UTC | Friday, April 24, 2020)\r\n\r\nSo, Prysm is correct. Wondering why Lighthouse would come up with a timestamp one hour later...",
